```julia
using Dates

function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int = 3)
    if !(dt isa DateTime)
        throw(ErrorException("Input must be a DateTime type"))
    end
    return dt + Hour(bump)
end
```

This function first checks if the input `dt` is of type `DateTime`. If not, it throws an error. Otherwise, it adds `bump` hours to the datetime using the `Hour` function from the Dates package. If `bump` is not provided, it defaults to 3 hours.
